WEBVTT

00:00:03.000 --> 00:00:08.600
Frontsmith is an AI front office for remodeling contractors, built to run inside Codex.

00:00:08.600 --> 00:00:20.200
Codex is the workspace where the owner can talk to the business kit in plain English. Frontsmith keeps the website, customer desk, estimates, launch notes, and approval records together.

00:00:20.200 --> 00:00:31.800
Start with the Owner Brief. Ask what needs attention today, and Codex turns the local records into a simple operating summary.

00:00:31.800 --> 00:00:44.400
Then move to the customer desk. Frontsmith can draft a clear follow-up, organize missing details, and keep the message as a draft until the owner approves the exact text.

00:00:44.400 --> 00:00:56.200
The same pattern applies to estimates, website updates, and connected actions. Codex prepares the work. Frontsmith shows the decision.

00:00:56.200 --> 00:01:06.800
A remodeling business can keep the digital front office moving from one workspace, without letting AI send, publish, schedule, connect, or change anything on its own.

00:01:06.800 --> 00:01:12.036
Frontsmith is a Codex-native operating kit for the work that has to be clear before customers see it.
